12
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:14,120
Doctor! Doctor!

13
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,760
- Something terrible's happened!
- Tsumura's disappeared!

14
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,800
It appears he's escaped!

15
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,160
He's escaped?

16
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:40,000
<i>BLOODSUCKING PAINTER KAZUHIKO 
TSUMURA FLEES MENTAL HOSPITAL</i>

17
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,360
What an odd incident.

18
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:53,120
For us, members of the Bizarro 
Enthusiast Club, it's a little intriguing.

19
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:55,320
This is no small thing -

20
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,240
it's a big deal, is what it is!

21
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,360
Not to mention the 
members of our club

22
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:08,080
have a connection with Dr. Kano...

23
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:41,560
MODEL AGENCY
"MUTUAL ARTS CLUB"

24
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,840
I'm after a model.

25
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,480
May I ask your name, or 
the name of your referral?

26
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,280
"I HEREBY REFER GHOSTMAN SAGAWA"
DR. SANSAKU KANO

27
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,560
I see - Dr. Kano referred you.
"I HEREBY REFER GHOSTMAN SAGAWA"
DR. SANSAKU KANO

28
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,280
I see - Dr. Kano referred you.

29
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,720
This will do fine.

30
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:05,680
But this "Ghostman"...

31
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:08,720
...this is your name?

32
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,040
Quite the strange pen name.

33
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:17,240
That's a very typical Dr. Kano referral.

34
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:22,280
- Will the model be for painting, or photography?
- Oil painting.

35
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,400
- From when?
- 2 hours, every day.

36
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,400
10 days, from today.

37
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,200
From today?

38
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,600
What's the address?

39
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,200
This way, please.

40
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,520
We have 6 models 
available for selection.

41
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,680
Keiko.

42
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,400
Yes.

43
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,800
There's something off about him.

44
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,080
I hope Keiko's alright.

45
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,040
What'll it be?

46
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,240
Thank you very much.

47
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,280
What're you doing 
out here? Any news?

48
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,920
You got a big mouth 
for a broke reporter.

49
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:10,000
You didn't see an odd 
man over there, did you?

50
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,400
- An odd man?
- Like a ghost.

51
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:14,440
- How macabre!
- No clue.

52
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,920
I see. Let's head back.

53
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:28,960
- I'm ready, Manager.
- He's too strange!

54
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:31,800
- You must reconsider.
- But...

55
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:34,080
...it's been so long between jobs.

56
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:39,800
- Hello.
- Hello, there.

57
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:43,360
Mr. Kikuchi - don't you think Keiko 
should turn that man down?

58
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,000
He's terribly weird.

59
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,360
What's going on?

60
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,640
What do you think?

61
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,920
There was a man here 
that looked like a ghost--

62
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,560
Stop it!

63
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,480
I'm going.

64
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,000
They're decent terms, after all.

65
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,520
If I lose any more work...

66
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,840
...my whole family is done for!

67
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:12,720
The address was Nishi-Ogikubo, 
wasn't it, manager?

68
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:19,440
Keiko! Wait, Keiko!

69
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,680
What's with you?

70
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,720
- I can't say.
- What's that?

71
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:28,840
Listen, you're just getting worked up.

72
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,920
That's not it -

73
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,120
I just feel like it's got to with that 
crazed man from the paper...

74
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,440
That's a good one.

75
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:41,800
Sounds like you'd be perfect 
for the Bizarro club too, Osada.

76
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:43,480
Good for you.

77
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:47,480
That's not what I'm talking about.

78
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:53,000
What's with the long face, Osada?

79
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,360
Are you cold?

80
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,040
Drink this. It'll warm you up.

81
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:00,120
Once you've finished, 
take your clothes off.

82
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,200
This way.

83
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,160
What will you do?

84
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:47,000
I'm feeling numb.

85
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:50,960
It's cleaning your blood.

86
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,600
My blood?

87
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,560
Are you going to kill me?

88
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:01,040
Don't kill me!

89
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:05,040
Please don't...please!

90
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:13,480
My mother's very old...

91
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:19,200
...and my little brothers...
there's lots of them!

92
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:22,160
You're looking terribly 
troubled, young man.

93
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:25,400
Your editor angry at you for 
not getting any good scoops?

94
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:29,560
- Nothing like that.
- What's with the long face and quick retorts, then?

95
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:36,320
I'm bored.

96
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,040
Write this, then:

97
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:43,000
"GHOST MAN VISITS 
NUDE MODEL CLUB"

98
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,760
Good, right? I'd read that newspaper!

99
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:49,040
Quit joking around.

100
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:57,360
Wanna dance?

101
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:03,200
They say nudes aren't even enough 
to sell papers these days.

102
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:15,360
Oh, it's the Doctor!

103
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,400
Dr. Kano himself graces 
us with his presence!

104
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:21,680
I'm sure you remember him, Mitsuko.

105
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,360
Shush.

106
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:32,120
Fewer girls here than usual. 
Someone off working?

107
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,360
Oh - that reminds me.

108
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,720
A strange man with 
your referral was here.

109
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,600
- My referral?
- That's right.

110
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:41,320
One "Ghostman Sagawa"...

111
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,280
Ghostman Sagawa?

112
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,960
Here.

113
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,040
Never seen it before.

114
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,080
What's wrong?

115
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:56,160
She'll be killed.

116
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:59,760
Come now, you 
shouldn't joke about that!

117
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:05,400
That ghost man was Tsumura - 
he ran an art class for women!

118
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,280
11:00pm already, huh?

119
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,600
She's late.

120
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,400
Good evening.

121
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:28,000
Have you seen your sister, Kokichi?

122
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,440
Nope.

123
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,000
I knew it.

124
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:36,400
What're you talking about? 
We don't know anything yet!

125
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,120
Did something 
happen to my sister?

126
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:42,200
Let's go and have a look, then!

127
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:44,440
- You have a car, Dr. Kano?
- Yes.

128
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,040
Let's get moving.

129
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:49,160
This concludes tonight's 
Bizarro Enthusiasts meeting.

130
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,560
Take me, too.

131
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,280
Good evening.

132
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,160
Who are you?

133
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,320
Who are you, 
and why are you here?

134
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,600
We're from a model agency -

135
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:51,200
a girl that we sent here on 
a job hasn't returned home.

136
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,880
A job? This house is abandoned.

137
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,880
The lights were on, 
so I thought I'd take a look.

138
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,640
Well, let's look inside and 
see what's going on.

139
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,720
That door ain't going to open.

140
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,920
How did you...?

141
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:08,800
Nothing to it.

142
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:33,760
Hey...isn't this Keiko's?

143
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:40,320
It is - it's hers!

144
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:45,760
So we at least know 
that she got naked here.

145
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:49,480
Don't say something so scary!

146
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,920
Sis!

147
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,000
<i>MODEL MURDERED IN THE NUDE</i>

148
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:41,560
<i>MURDERED BEAUTY IN THE BATHTUB: CRAZED 
SPIDER-OWNING PAINTER, WHEREABOUTS UNKNOWN</i>

149
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:04,480
And why mustn't I associate with 
the Bizarro Enthusiast Club?

150
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:06,400
By all means, you can -

151
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:10,240
but you're at the international 
forefront of psychiatry:

152
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:16,120
if you get too curious, you'll 
start to want greater thrills.

153
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:22,280
This vampiric Tsumura fellow 
was also a member, I recall.

154
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:34,640
And just what do you take 
the Bizarro Enthusiasts for?

155
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:39,120
You've been so careless about the club, 
now the police are looking in our direction!

156
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,640
Hirota.

157
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:45,040
You must tell every newspaper that the
 club has nothing to do with the ghost man.

158
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,440
Yes, sir.

159
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,720
It's too late, Dr. Kano.

160
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:52,240
It was one of our models 
that was killed, after all.

161
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,520
What's that? How dare 
you be so blasÃ©!

162
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:57,080
In any case, the club has 
nothing to do with this case.

163
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:59,040
Maybe, maybe not.

164
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,000
It's only natural for them to be 
suspicious of high-profile members.

165
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:07,080
What? What exactly are you--!

166
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,800
Are you alright?

167
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,680
I'm fine.

168
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:27,520
<i>Greetings, models from 
the Mutual Arts Club.</i>

169
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:30,520
<i>This is the Ghost Man.</i>

170
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:37,720
<i>I trust you all enjoyed the superb 
performance I put on for Act 1 of the show...</i>

171
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,560
- Come out of there!
- Wait - it's dangerous!

172
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:47,960
<i>And now, preparations for 
Act 2 have been completed,</i>

173
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:52,400
<i>and I am now 
looking for a co-star.</i>

174
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:52,920
<i>I truly hope the next one 
will be as splendid as the first.</i>

175
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,360
It's just a tape.
<i>I truly hope the next one 
will be as splendid as the first.</i>

176
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,360
<i>I truly hope the next one 
will be as splendid as the first.</i>

177
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,480
Let's listen to the end.
<i>I truly hope the next one 
will be as splendid as the first.</i>

178
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:57,600
Let's listen to the end.

179
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:03,440
<i>I look forward to your attendance. 
That's all from me - good night!</i>

180
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,080
Tea, please.

181
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,520
Hello? Yes, it's me.

182
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,560
Inspector Todoroki.

183
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:32,240
I'd like you to look 
into one more guy.

184
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:35,280
Matsubacho 23, Taito-ku.

185
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:37,920
Goes by the name of 
Kentaro Yamagata.

186
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:41,480
The kanji for "ken" is "<i>kane</i>". 
That'll be it for today.

187
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,120
Look into him carefully. 
I'll be here a while more.

188
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:48,720
Evening, Inspector.

189
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,480
Y'know...

190
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:55,280
...you needn't work so hard 
sifting through all your suspects.

191
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,560
The tape serves as 
great evidence, doesn't it?

192
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:02,240
Isn't there a more...
scientific way of investigating?

193
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:06,240
That might be enough for the 
Bizarro Enthusiasts, but not for us.

194
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:10,920
We've got to be preemptive about this 
second murder he's announced, in any case.

195
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:13,600
Exactly! Mr. Kikuchi's 
acting all indifferent about it,

196
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,960
even though we're the ones being hunted!
- That's right!

197
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,920
Take it a little more seriously, OK?

198
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,560
Alright, alright. My apologies.

199
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,600
Yes? Yes, that's right.

200
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:27,920
Hello, sir. Inspector Todoroki - 
it's from headquarters.

201
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,480
Thank you.

202
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,360
Yes, hello? Yes.

203
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:35,600
Yes. Hm? Taro Yamada?

204
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:38,840
Yes...yes...what?

205
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,280
Ah...yes. Alright, understood.

206
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:44,120
No such person as 
"Taro Yamada", apparently.

207
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:46,360
Which girl is he hiring?

208
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:50,200
Let's see...

209
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,480
...it's Mitsuko!

210
00:23:57,720 --> 00:24:00,240
Nothing to worry about!

211
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:02,640
Could just be a prank.

212
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:05,360
It doesn't mean 
he's after you next!

213
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:09,960
Not to mention the fine fellows from 
the police force will be there with you.

214
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,520
Do you remember what 
kind of man he was?

215
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,520
Well...

216
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:19,160
...it says he called us on the 23rd.

217
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:21,800
I wonder which one he was...

218
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,680
Do you remember him?

219
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:29,560
How about you? And you?

220
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:32,120
Don't you remember him?

221
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,440
Now you mention it...

222
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,280
...there was one weird guy, right?
- Ah! Him!

223
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,400
Stop it!

224
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:46,520
I'm going to be killed...!

225
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:52,360
<i>TARO YAMADA, PAINTER, AOYAMA.
MODEL NAME: MITSUKO MIYAKAWA</i>

226
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:00,520
I'll keep you company overnight.

227
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:03,080
- You'll be fine.
- Thank you.

228
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,080
Don't leave me alone!

229
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,000
Mr. Kikuchi.

230
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,480
What a fright you gave me!

231
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:15,800
Anything out of the ordinary?

232
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:18,600
Of course not! Don't be silly.

233
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:20,600
Really?

234
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:24,040
Can you come along too, Kokichi?

235
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,920
Please...I'm scared.

236
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,920
Go on, then.

237
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,040
Sure, no problem.

238
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:39,000
Huh? Where are we going?

239
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,280
What's wrong?

240
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:58,640
You...!

241
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,080
Who are you?

242
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:23,080
Taro Yamada.

243
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:45,200
Please...spare my life!

244
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:48,760
I'll do anything! 
I don't want to die!

245
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:51,720
Keiko said the same thing.

246
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:54,880
I like the way women look 
when they are freshly dead.

247
00:28:55,000 --> 00:29:00,000
No! I don't want to die!

248
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,280
Fine.

249
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,640
They won't find me, 
anyway - I give up.

250
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,120
Your face...

251
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,760
...take off those bandages!

252
