knowing who killed me!

253
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,840
Very well.

254
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,440
It makes no difference, I suppose.

255
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:34,440
I'll take them off for you.

256
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,360
Hello? Hello?

257
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:38,520
Hey, mister!

258
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,320
- She'll be killed.
- Huh?

259
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:42,920
She'll be killed!

260
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:45,520
- Mitsuko will be killed...
- Hello?

261
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:47,520
Pull yourself together. Who's that?

262
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,720
Who's Mitsuko?

263
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,680
Three-fingered man...

264
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,480
...three-fingered man...
- Three-fingered man?

265
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,320
Tsumura, the Ghost Man!

266
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:58,920
Hello? And who are you?

267
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,040
If he's telling the truth, 
something bad's happened!

268
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:04,240
There's been an incident in Mitaka. 
We just heard from the bureau.

269
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,840
Busy day today.

270
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:10,200
Call an ambulance, and 
tell HQ to look into this man.

271
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:33,200
- What's their condition?
- Nothing serious.

272
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:36,960
Hey, you can't take photos yet!

273
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,240
Are they alright?

274
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,240
They've just been drugged.

275
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:45,400
They'll come to in about an hour.

276
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:48,360
How did you know about this?

277
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,400
This is the work of the Ghost Man.

278
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,640
Huh?

279
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,960
The Ghost Man phoned last night...

280
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,280
Why didn't you tell us?

281
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,520
Didn't think he would spare them.

282
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,960
I don't suppose you're related 
to this Ghost Man, are you?

283
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:07,040
Take care of this for me, would you?

284
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:13,000
Get started, then.

285
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:37,080
This isn't a joke.

286
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:41,480
You think I'm related to 
the Ghost Man, too?

287
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,200
No, you idiot.

288
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:48,360
I think you shouldn't keep 
sticking your nose into this.

289
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:51,480
I'm a newspaper reporter.

290
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:55,880
You've only been focused on 
the Ghost Man incidents, though.

291
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:57,920
Anybody would think that's odd.

292
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,680
You want me to be a small 
fry reporter forever?

293
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,240
I'm worried.

294
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:27,680
Ayuko...

295
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:33,760
Y'know, Ken, I'm...

296
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:38,480
Forget it. I shouldn't just blurt 
things out like you do.

297
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:40,360
Ayuko!

298
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:50,840
So...Tsumura and the Ghost Man 
are two different people, then?

299
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:52,200
Yes.

300
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:56,120
I didn't make it to the 
hideout, so I can't be sure,

301
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:58,520
but that's what Kokichi says.

302
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,960
Let's stop talking about it, OK?

303
00:34:01,400 --> 00:34:02,680
Alright.

304
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:06,720
You were after a big scoop when 
you heard about the incident, right?

305
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:10,320
Guess you'll have to wait a bit longer.
- What are you on about?

306
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:14,840
In any case, I wish Dr. Kano would hurry 
back from Osaka and take us to a shoot.

307
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:17,360
I can't bear being 
shut up in here.

308
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:20,000
Couldn't we do a shoot 
somewhere far away?

309
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:22,200
Dr. Kano said he's 
thinking of a hotel in Izu.

310
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:24,040
It'd be lovely there.

311
