Fire!

500
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:27,840
Hey! Everyone!

501
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:30,000
It's not a big fire!

502
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:32,200
Hey, listen! Calm down!

503
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:35,440
Hey! It's not a big deal!

504
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:39,040
There you are.

505
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:41,600
I decided to stay put 
to avoid the rabble.

506
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:44,040
- Good idea.
- Sorry for worrying you.

507
00:52:44,520 --> 00:52:46,000
Don't mention it.

508
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:49,000
Detective! It was just smoke!

509
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:52,520
They really pulled a dumb prank 
this time. This is all it was.

510
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,520
- Show me.
-Here.

511
00:52:59,120 --> 00:53:01,240
Is this one of the theater's?

512
00:53:01,360 --> 00:53:02,480
Well...

513
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:05,520
...ours are much smaller. 
We can't use those kinds.

514
00:53:05,600 --> 00:53:08,360
You know what I think, Detective?

515
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:11,440
The theater's getting old 
and run down these days -

516
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:15,680
I think some trickster just 
wanted part of the action tonight.

517
00:53:15,720 --> 00:53:20,640
I love these kinds of whodunit cases! 
We're gonna catch this fellow for sure!

518
00:53:26,560 --> 00:53:30,080
<i>WE APOLOGIZE FOR THE DISTURBANCE
NO DAMAGE INCURRED - THE SHOW WILL CONTINUE</i>

519
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:56,760
Yes?

520
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:01,680
Everything alright?

521
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,120
The girl third from the 
left is pretty charming.

522
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:29,880
What's her name?

523
00:54:30,080 --> 00:54:33,080
- You got eyes for her?
- She's already got 3 guys, you know.

524
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:35,080
Only 3?

525
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:37,960
Welcome.

526
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:45,760
But that's so cruel, Ayuko...!

527
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:49,560
The world's a 
cruel place, you know.

528
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:52,320
You can't see it through 
your naivety, though.

529
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:55,240
What a single woman has 
to do to make a living...

530
00:54:55,600 --> 00:54:58,640
...it's both thrilling, and terrifying.

531
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,640
Why, even you, Ken...

532
00:55:01,440 --> 00:55:02,680
Stop talking nonsense!

533
00:55:02,880 --> 00:55:05,080
I don't want your life
 to be in danger!

534
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:19,920
Watch my performance carefully, Ken.

535
00:55:21,760 --> 00:55:24,160
It's going to be wonderful.

536
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:30,120
They're ready for you, Ayuko.

537
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:32,480
Let's head out.

538
00:55:32,760 --> 00:55:35,120
Could you get Mr. Kajiwara for me?

539
00:55:39,680 --> 00:55:40,520
Yes?

540
00:55:40,680 --> 00:55:42,720
Mr. Kajiwara, Ayuko sent for you.

541
00:55:47,320 --> 00:55:48,680
Come in.

542
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:50,600
What is it?

543
00:55:50,640 --> 00:55:52,960
Ah - I just wanted 
to rehearse a bit.

544
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:54,560
Alright.

545
00:55:55,720 --> 00:55:57,480
Let's see...

546
00:58:12,560 --> 00:58:14,320
Huh? It's a mannequin!

547
00:58:14,600 --> 00:58:15,720
Where's Kajiwara?

548
00:58:15,760 --> 00:58:18,360
The manager went to look for him!

549
00:58:20,920 --> 00:58:22,800
To think he'd use 
a mannequin like this...

550
00:58:22,920 --> 00:58:26,240
- How bizarre.
- Where's the real Ayuko, I wonder?

551
00:58:27,720 --> 00:58:30,600
- Manager! Where's Kajiwara?
- I found him, but--

552
00:58:38,640 --> 00:58:40,880
- Anybody else been here but you?
- No.

553
00:58:42,600 --> 00:58:44,320
Looks like the 
next act is starting.

554
00:58:44,560 --> 00:58:46,080
Damn it!

555
00:59:23,880 --> 00:59:25,360
Get her down, quick!

556
00:59:45,960 --> 00:59:47,200
Ayuko!

557
00:59:47,680 --> 00:59:50,240
Ayuko...Ayuko!

558
00:59:50,760 --> 00:59:52,880
Hands off the crime scene!

559
00:59:52,960 --> 00:59:54,320
What's this?

560
00:59:55,040 --> 00:59:57,480
Wait...no!

561
00:59:58,120 --> 01:00:01,080
No! It wasn't me!

562
01:00:01,280 --> 01:00:02,520
Shut it.

563
01:00:02,760 --> 01:00:05,360
Those three teeth are enough 
to pin you to the crime.

564
01:00:05,680 --> 01:00:07,360
If you please, Inspector.

565
01:00:08,040 --> 01:00:12,200
Wait! No! It wasn't me!

566
01:00:12,360 --> 01:00:15,040
You've got the wrong guy!

567
01:00:17,520 --> 01:00:19,520
<i>CRIMINAL INVESTIGATIONS
ROOM 6</i>

568
01:00:28,480 --> 01:00:30,000
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

569
01:00:33,120 --> 01:00:34,240
Here.

570
01:00:36,880 --> 01:00:40,200
Alright. I was 
the first Ghost Man,

571
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:42,320
but that was it!

572
01:00:42,520 --> 01:00:45,920
I only threatened Keiko - 
I would never kill her!

573
01:00:46,240 --> 01:00:47,440
He's still out there.

574
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:49,560
Who's responsible for 
the second murder, then?

575
01:00:49,600 --> 01:00:51,920
- Not me, that's for sure!
- Whatever you say.

576
01:00:52,120 --> 01:00:54,520
I don't care if it's one guy 
or Ghostman brothers.

577
01:00:54,880 --> 01:00:57,720
How'd you come up 
with something like that?

578
01:01:01,680 --> 01:01:03,320
As a newspaper reporter...

579
01:01:03,400 --> 01:01:06,200
...I wanted to 
get the best scoop.

580
01:01:06,360 --> 01:01:09,440
Isn't your father working a 
high position at your paper?

581
01:01:09,680 --> 01:01:13,040
- Why'd you try so hard?
- That's exactly why I panicked!

582
01:01:13,800 --> 01:01:16,440
I couldn't stand 
disappointing my father.

583
01:01:16,760 --> 01:01:18,880
<i>"...more on that as 
developments happen.</i>

584
01:01:18,920 --> 01:01:21,820
<i>Next, the hospital escapee 
and vampire Kazuhiko Tsumura,</i>

585
01:01:21,820 --> 01:01:24,320
<i>who has the whole of 
Tokyo gripped in fear,</i>

586
01:01:24,360 --> 01:01:28,490
<i>has struck once again - this time, 
the queen of the Reijin Theater, Ayuko -</i>

587
01:01:28,490 --> 01:01:31,840
<i>despite arousing strict 
vigilance amongst Tokyo police.</i>

588
01:01:32,040 --> 01:01:34,960
<i>Due to the superb effort of the 
investigation squad, however,</i>

589
01:01:35,040 --> 01:01:37,240
<i>he was quickly arrested 
afterward as prime suspect.</i>

590
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:39,560
<i>The culprit, Kazuhiko Tsumura, has--"</i>

591
01:01:48,200 --> 01:01:51,120
<i>BEAUTY IN THE BATHTUB</i>

592
01:01:51,840 --> 01:01:55,840
<i>GARDEN OF THE GROTESQUE</i>

593
01:01:56,160 --> 01:02:00,400
<i>WOMAN BATHING</i>

594
01:02:00,600 --> 01:02:04,720
<i>LEOPARD AND WOMAN</i>

595
01:02:04,960 --> 01:02:09,200
<i>BALLOON AND WOMAN</i>

596
01:02:09,400 --> 01:02:12,560
<i>BED AND WOMAN</i>

597
01:02:21,040 --> 01:02:23,680
It's your turn next.

598
01:02:35,160 --> 01:02:37,320
Kind of a disappointing result.

599
01:02:37,560 --> 01:02:40,000
- He's not admitting anything!
- I should think not.

600
01:02:40,200 --> 01:02:42,320
- He doesn't know anything, after all.
- Huh?

601
01:02:42,600 --> 01:02:45,960
He's the victim here. I asked 
him to do a little job for me.

602
01:02:46,160 --> 01:02:48,600
You think we're 
safe releasing him?

603
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:51,000
He'll lead us to the Ghost Man 
any minute now, I think.

604
01:02:51,040 --> 01:02:53,720
Yes? It's for you, Mr. Kindaichi.

605
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:56,880
Yes?

606
01:02:58,120 --> 01:02:59,320
What?

607
01:02:59,360 --> 01:03:01,920
So he was at Yanokura!

608
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:04,080
I'll be there right away.

609
01:03:04,920 --> 01:03:07,520
I'll be off then, Inspector Todoroki.

610
01:04:14,200 --> 01:04:16,240
What did you do with him?

611
01:04:42,160 --> 01:04:44,120
What do you plan 
to do with him?

612
01:04:44,800 --> 01:04:48,240
This man is getting in my way!

613
01:04:48,320 --> 01:04:51,680
Let me go! Just 
exactly who are you?

614
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:55,320
Everyone calls me Ghost Man.

615
01:04:55,520 --> 01:04:57,040
Coward!

616
01:04:58,560 --> 01:04:59,640
Kinuko!

617
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:01,760
Kinuko...do you 
know what it's like?

618
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:05,000
For a man to truly 
love a woman?

619
01:05:05,160 --> 01:05:07,760
What? Let me go!

620
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:09,440
Let me go!

621
01:05:11,960 --> 01:05:14,920
Get a good look, Doctor.

622
01:05:15,160 --> 01:05:18,640
I'm going to do whatever I like 
with her right in front of you!

623
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:21,240
Get off me!

624
01:05:21,400 --> 01:05:23,400
I'm married, you know!

625
01:05:23,600 --> 01:05:25,920
And your husband Tsumura
 is a crazed maniac.

626
01:05:26,040 --> 01:05:27,520
So then...

627
01:05:28,280 --> 01:05:31,200
...what exactly is 
that man to you?

628
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:32,880
Your lover?

629
01:05:32,920 --> 01:05:35,520
I divorced Tsumura!

630
01:05:35,640 --> 01:05:39,680
And he went mad as a result. 
Is that what you wanted?

631
01:05:40,560 --> 01:05:43,200
Why don't we see 
what he thinks?

632
01:05:44,840 --> 01:05:47,520
Tsumura! Tsumura!

633
01:05:54,840 --> 01:05:56,840
Mind if I answer for him?

634
01:05:57,080 --> 01:05:58,600
You!

635
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:01,920
I've finally seen him -

636
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:04,040
the famous Ghost Man killer.

637
01:06:04,280 --> 01:06:06,760
No! The killer is Tsumura!

638
01:06:06,960 --> 01:06:09,760
- We heard it all from Tsumura.
- What are you going on about?

639
01:06:10,120 --> 01:06:14,200
- This man is a crazed maniac!
- And who used that maniac?

640
01:06:18,200 --> 01:06:19,920
Give it up, you murderer!

641
01:06:20,240 --> 01:06:21,920
Be a man and 
turn yourself in.

642
01:09:11,280 --> 01:09:12,880
It wasn't me!

643
01:09:13,200 --> 01:09:15,000
It wasn't me!

644
01:09:15,280 --> 01:09:18,080
I didn't mean to kill anyone!

645
01:09:18,360 --> 01:09:22,400
Why'd you take Tsumura's 
ex-wife hostage, then?

646
01:09:22,680 --> 01:09:24,240
She's my girl.

647
01:09:24,360 --> 01:09:28,480
I'm in love with her - she's 
the one I ought to be with!

648
01:09:28,760 --> 01:09:31,280
The woman that's trying to 
become Dr. Kano's wife?

649
01:09:31,640 --> 01:09:34,840
Tsumura's the one that 
took those women!

650
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:38,840
Tsumura was known for his thirst for blood, 
but you were the one pulling the strings.

651
01:09:39,120 --> 01:09:42,320
You're a fiend. All in the 
needless pursuit of one woman.

652
01:09:42,440 --> 01:09:44,840
It wasn't me - 
it was Ken Tatebe!

653
01:09:45,160 --> 01:09:47,680
Ken might have 
played the first prank,

654
01:09:47,960 --> 01:09:50,400
but you assumed the lead role.

655
01:09:50,600 --> 01:09:52,360
I know everything.

656
01:09:52,680 --> 01:09:55,360
Lies! Lies!

657
01:09:55,600 --> 01:09:57,000
Lies!

658
01:10:09,040 --> 01:10:10,080
I'll shoot!

659
01:10:10,120 --> 01:10:13,160
Throw down your gun!
This is the end of line!

660
01:12:05,520 --> 01:12:12,280
<i>FIN</i>

